brief:
Timer class for profiling algorithm components

TimedTask provides RAII-style timing measurement for code blocks.
Tracks CPU time, system time, and wall clock time. Multiple
Start()/End() pairs accumulate total time across invocations.

Usage:
  TimedTask timer;
  timer.Start();
  // ... expensive operation ...
  timer.End();
  double elapsed = timer.TotalCpuTime();

Used throughout Ipopt to report timing breakdown by category
(function evaluation, linear solve, line search, etc.).
